define.name: CATINT32ToPtr
define.abstract: Use this macro to cast a 32-bits integer type to a pointer.

define.name: CATLONG32ToPtr
define.abstract: Use this macro to cast a 32-bits signed long type to a pointer.

define.name: CATPtrToINT32
define.abstract: Use this macro to convert a pointer to a 32-bit unsigned integer for arithmetic manipulation.

define.name: CATPtrToLONG32
define.abstract: Use this macro to convert a pointer to a 32-bit signed long integer for arithmetic manipulation.

define.name: CATPtrToUINT32
define.abstract: Use this macro to convert a pointer to a 32-bit unsigned integer for arithmetic manipulation.

define.name: CATPtrToULONG32
define.abstract: Use this macro to convert a pointer to a 32-bit unsigned long integer for arithmetic manipulation.

define.name: CATUINT32ToPtr
define.abstract: Use this macro to cast a 32-bits unsigned integer type to a pointer.

define.name: CATULONG32ToPtr
define.abstract: Use this macro to cast a 32-bits unsigned long type to a pointer.

define.name: FAILED
define.abstract: Generic test for failure on any status value (negative numbers indicate failure).

define.name: SUCCEEDED
define.abstract: Generic test for success on any status value (non-negative numbers indicate success).

typedef.name: BYTE

typedef.abstract: Signed long type having pointer precision.

typedef.name: CATUINTPTR
typedef.abstract: unsigned int type having pointer precision.

typedef.name: CATULONGINT

typedef.abstract: Unsigned long type having pointer precision.
